[1] note that in a less than perfect world (ask me about abelian
teleology!), the Nitrogen in the air also gets involved.  If it combines
with:                you  get:      Resulting in
Oxygen               NOx            pollution
Hydrogen and Oxygen  HNO3           Nitric Acid!
Carbon               CN             Cyanide[2]

If you are lucky, this exits to pollute the atmosphere. If you are not, it
winds up in the crankcase and at least the HNO3 (nitric acid) is a BAD
THING when combined with your metal parts.

[2] My gut tells me this should happen, but I have never heard about it,
and you would think this would be NEWS if it were happening at a
detectable level.  Maybe it is not stable?  or requires more heat than is
readily available?  I dunno, I am not more than an armchair chemist.

